===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|nexus||the act of binding together; bond|lang=la}}, from {{term|necto|nectō|bind|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈnɛksəs/}}
* {{rhymes|ɛksəs}}

===Noun===
{{head|en|noun|plural|nexuses|or|nexus}}

# a form of [[connection]]
# a [[connect]]ed [[group]]
# the [[centre]] of [[something]]

====Usage notes====
The Latin plural form (written ''[[nexûs]]'' or ''[[nexūs]]'') is sometimes used in academic discussions of process philosophy (see {{pedialite|Nexus (process philosophy)}}).

